2012-01-30|2012-02-05.description:
Student vs. Student vs. Staff- but why?

A surprise cliffhanger that will have your jaw on the floor!
2012-01-30|2012-02-05.name: Class Reunion

2012-02-20|2012-02-26.description:
The X-Men will stop at nothing to find Jubilee, even if they have to kill every vampire on Earth to do so!

X-Men vs. Vampires in a major way!
2012-02-20|2012-02-26.name: Open Contract, Part One

2012-03-26|2012-04-01.description: This is it! "The Death Race" comes to a stunning conclusion as we learn the truth about the origin of vampire hunter Travis Kidd. Plus: Some old friends return and a shocking ending that's not to be missed!
2012-03-26|2012-04-01.name: Death Race, Part Four of Four

2012-04-02|2012-04-08.description:
"MAJOR LEAGUE CHEW" Part Five For sale: One Cibopath, slightly used, extremely damaged.

While Tony is missing, Amelia goes around town, and also calling Tony's friends and family, to find out information on Tony's last location. When nothing turns up on her missing boyfriend, she heads back to work to take her mind off things. Amelia's ex-boyfriend, Dan, makes the mistake in talking about Tony's disappearance. Knowing that Dan talking about Tony's disappearance was no coincidence, Amelia follows her ex-boyfriend to an abandoned theatre where he is auctioning off Tony.

While Dan made his speech about dreams and following them, Amelia was outside gaining information about what is going on inside the theatre. Knowing that she couldn't get inside without a disguise, she used her abilities as a Saboscrivner to borrow a costume and walk through the front door. Dan was about to collect his pay from a group of private scientist that bought Tony, but was interrupted when Amelia busted in the door and demanded they release her boyfriend before she opens fire. Knowing that the gun was a decoy, Dan was about to rape Amelia, but a badly injured Tony Chu uses the remaining strength he had left and throws a baseball at Dan's head ending up killing him. In the end, Amelia rushes Tony to the hospital and John Colby gains a new partner; Poyo!
2012-04-02|2012-04-08.name: Major League Chew, Part 5 of 5

2012-04-09|2012-04-15.description: The Final Ascension Of The Adaptoids, Deathlok Legion, Sentinaughts, Ultravisions, And Machine People! Can The Secret Avengers Stop These Descendants From Carrying Out Contagious Robotic Evolution? A Dead Friend Returns! An Avenger Mortally Injured! A Spy In Their Midst! The Lighthouse Compromised! A New Race Is Born!
2012-04-09|2012-04-15.name: Grandfather Clause

2012-04-09|2012-04-15.description:
500 Years Later. Mars.

The plot:

Riley has a dream...

In the 26th century, Mars is inhabited by humans and other aliens.

For some reason, Riley is still alive and kicking. She has traveled to Mars, to do something.

She needs and wants a fast way of transportation. The seller wants too much money for the vehicle he/she/other gender is selling. Riley wont have that. She shows that she isn`t someone to mess around with. She gets the vehicle with a reasonable prize.

She drives the helibike (or whatever it`s called) to the desert.

She meets Glory once again, like she intended. They haven`t seen each other for centuries. They talk. Talk about the fact that Glory caused the downfall of humans. That even if she won (or, as Riley says, "won") the war between two destructive forces, she destroyed most of human civilization. Things never became better on Earth.

We see Supreme and Glory act brutally against one another.

When they`re done with talking, Riley asks Glory to do what she wants her to do.

Glory kills Riley.

Then she burns her corpse, and sheds a tear.

Riley wakes up. She knows that what she saw may be the future. She panics, and runs to Glorias room. She tells about her dream. Gloria tells Riley that her mission is to stop Glory from making the future very grim indeed.
2012-04-09|2012-04-15.name: Once and Future, Part Three: 'The Way It Will Be'

2012-04-16|2012-04-22.description: The war between the Avengers and the X-Men has started and it gets through the books of both Avengers titles and X-Men related titles as the battle starts.

2012-04-23|2012-04-29.description: Avx Tie-In! Iron Fist Discovers The Shocking Connection Between Himself And The Cosmic Phoenix Force!
2012-04-23|2012-04-29.name: Dragon vs Phoenix

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description: The 99 are on the move, they have outgrown their Paris headquarters and Dr. Ramzi decides to relocate the foundation to Spain. But like all moves, not everything goes as planned and there's a dramatic rescue along the way. Dr. Ramzi also learns that an ancient book about the Noor Stones he's been studying has a more sinister origin than he imagined.
2012-05-07|2012-05-13.name: What Is Written

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description:
The epic saga THE FINAL EXECUTION begins here!

Who are the Omegas and why must X-Force hunt them down?

Included in this issue: Two rare stories by Rick Remender and Jerome Opeña starring Wolverine and Deadpool!
2012-05-07|2012-05-13.name: Purity / Appetite for Destruction

2012-05-07|2012-05-13.description: Ever since Gwen came back from the dead as a zombie, she's been hearing cryptic hints about something bad on the way. Well, now it's here, and Gwen and her friends are right in the middle of it. After this, nothing will be the same – especially between Gwen and her ex-monster hunter boyfriend Horatio.
2012-05-07|2012-05-13.name: The End, Part 1

2012-05-21|2012-05-27.description: Robert Jordan's fantasy epic continues here! Rand and Mat are running themselves ragged, unable to afford lodging or food, and unable to perform for any money without attracting darkfriends... but they are close, so close, to Caemlyn. It's the last village before the city, and evil is lurking everywhere - especially in their dreams. Will they make it to the city before they're found out? The journey continues in Robert Jordan's THE WHEEL OF TIME: THE EYE OF THE WORLD!

volume.name: Robert Jordan's Wheel of Time: The Eye of the World

2012-05-21|2012-05-27.description: Prophet is trapped on an alien slave ship manufacturing living missiles in the middle of a massive space war.
2012-05-21|2012-05-27.name: [untitled] / Initiate, Part II: Boaz

2012-05-21|2012-05-27.description: Green Hornet battles Green Hornet, to the death. The people of Century City are convinced that Britt Reid, as Green Hornet, murdered the city's Mayor. The only way for Britt to clear his name is to track down the real killer. When Green Hornet comes face to face with his doppelganger, it may just turn out to be the last fight of his life. If Britt Reid can't defeat the costumed imposter that framed him, a hero's legacy will be destroyed forever, and Century City will fall into the hands of the evil mastermind who orchestrated the whole setup. The Outcast storyline rolls on toward its thunderous conclusion.
2012-05-21|2012-05-27.name: Outcast, Part Four of Six

2012-05-28|2012-06-03.description: 'Kyla Nicolle: Canada's Next Great Super Model?' It's the question everyone is asking in The Great White North. Watch the feisty redhead in head-to-head action against Zootanapuss as 'Zootanapuss vs. High Fashion Models' nears its climax. 'When Sudden Death Isn't Enough For a Girl and Her Bonny: SHOOT-OUT!' In the History of Photorealism section, a close examination of Stan Drake's version of the car crash that claimed the life of Alex Raymond as documented in Arlen Schumer's 'Alex Raymond's Last Ride.'

2012-07-23|2012-07-29.name: Insecticided

2012-08-13|2012-08-19.description:
A PRESIDENTIAL MIX-UP

In this volume of Air Gear, the unthinkable has occurred: the minds of Emily Adachi and United States President Omaha have switched bodies! Omaha speaks about his desire for Air Treck technology to be used for the good of all humanity. Meanwhile, Team Trident is plunged into a bloody battle as mysterious invaders descend upon Osaka!

This volume of Air Gear includes special extras after the story!
2012-08-13|2012-08-19.name: A Presidential Mix-Up

2012-09-17|2012-09-23.description: The effects of the Savage Six continue to ripple through the life of Flash Thompson! And as the supernatural ante is upped, the world hangs in the balance!
2012-09-17|2012-09-23.name: Monsters of Evil, Part 3

2012-09-24|2012-09-30.description: Winter Wolves: Part 2 - The world believes the notorious outlaw Billy the Kid was killed by Pat Garrett, the Kid is very much alive, the hired gun of a traveling spectacle of biological curiosities—or “freaks,” as Billy calls them. Billy and crew head to Loch Ness to rescue their lizard-skinned comrade from Count Dracula.
2012-09-24|2012-09-30.name: Winter Wolves, Part Two

2012-10-01|2012-10-07.description: No tricks here-- this 113 page Digital Exclusive is a real treat! Join Archie and the gang in some spooky fun. From haunted houses to Halloween parties, Riverdale knows how to do the monster mash! What will everyone dress up as this year? Read on to find out! Featuring a special guest appearance by Sabrina the Teenage Witch!
2012-10-01|2012-10-07.name: Archie Halloween Blowout

2012-10-22|2012-10-28.description: As the Osaka Gantz team falls to the alien monster boss, Kaze of the Tokyo team takes the fight to the superbeast to save the mortally wounded little Takeshi. But even the powerful Kaze is no match for the shape-shifting fiend, and the Tokyo team musters a desperate offensive that could turn the tide . . . or seal their doom!
2012-10-22|2012-10-28.name: Volume 25

2012-11-19|2012-11-25.description: "Dreaming He is a Butterfly" part 1 of 2. Scarecrow believes that fear is your friend, and he wants to help Batman get in touch with that emotion. Will his new fear toxin succeed where the old version failed?
2012-11-19|2012-11-25.name: Dreaming He is a Butterfly, Part 1 of 2

2012-12-03|2012-12-09.description: After watching a video of Sannoh’s semifinal game from the previous year, the Shohoku players, except Sakuragi of course, are feeling nervous—three of Sannoh’s starters this year played on that championship team. To make things worse, the stands are filled with Sannoh supporters eager to see their favorite rack up an easy win against Shohoku. But Coach Anzai’s been here before and he knows his players, instructing them to lead off with a surprise attack that lets Sannoh know that Shohoku’s in the house, and they aren’t going out without a fight!
2012-12-03|2012-12-09.name: Vol. 25

2012-12-10|2012-12-16.description: 'Archie Marries Veronica.' After the smashing success of their television debut, Betty and Reggie have a decision to make whether they want to continue down the reality TV path. As Archie and Veronica start up their new business ventures, things seem to be looking up for the happy couple for the first time in a long while. 'Archie Marries Betty.' Jughead makes the transition to fatherhood with a baby on the way, meaning he's also looking out for his kid sister's best interest whose boyfriend is sketchy at best. While Cheryl stays positive about her fight with breast cancer, someone close to the gang is about to have a brush with death.

"Haunted" part 1! Lex Luthor dives far into his own mind, trying to force Tess into revealing her secrets. Just as he's about to make a breakthrough, he's forced to confront a former ... experiment ... named Psimon, who's after his blood. If only Lex could remember him! Will Superman be able to stop Psimon, or will he need the help of a very fast friend?
2012-12-10|2012-12-16.name: Haunted Part 1

2012-12-17|2012-12-23.description: HELL ON EARTH concludes here, bringing the second year of Dynamite's Vampirella series to a close! The two most powerful vampires on Earth are clashing in a fury of blood and fire, and the balance of Chaos and Order is at stake!
2012-12-17|2012-12-23.name: Hell On Earth, Part 2: The End is the Beginning is the End
